                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1"> <locus target="#4r">Fol. 4r</locus>: Purchase note. <q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 4r: ፲፱፴፬፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ሐምሌ፡ ፴ቀን፡ እኔ፡ አለቃ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ወልደ፡ ሥላሴ፡ መዝሙር፡ በ፵፭፡ ስጨ፡ አሎኍ፡ ለቀኘዝማች፡ የዕብዩ፡ ተስፋ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ኃይለ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ይሙት፡ ብሩም፡ ፵፭፡ ደረሰኝ፡ እኔ፡ አለቃ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ …</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in Amharic and is dated 30 Ḥamle 1934 year of Mercy (= 6th August 1942). It states that ʾaläqa Gäbrä Maryam Wäldä Śǝllase sold this book to qäňňazmač Yäʿbǝyyo Täsfa Mikaʾel for 45 birr. It also mentions ʾaläqa Kahǝsay ʾAbrǝha as guarantor of the book. The fingerprints of the seller, the buyer and the guarantor are placed at the end of the note.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2"> <locus target="#4v">Fol. 4v</locus>: Donation note. <q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 4v: ዝመዝሙር፡ ዘቀኘዝማች፡ የዕብዮ፡ ተስፋ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ደንዴራ፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note states that qäňňazmač Yäʿbǝyyo Täsfa Mikaʾel donated this book to the church of Qǝddus Mikaʾel Dändera. The ink is partly faded away.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3"> <locus target="#5r">Fol. 5r</locus>: Ownership note. <q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 5r: ዘንቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ መዝሙር፡ ዘቀኘዝማች፡ የዕብየዮ፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is crudely written in pencil in the upper margin of the folio. It states that the book belongs to qäňňazmač Yäʿbǝyyo.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4"> <locus target="#94r">Fol. 94r</locus>: Prayer. <q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 94r: ዘበሱራፌል፡ ወኬሩቤል፡ የዓርፍ፡ ወያከርሞ፡ በበዓመት፡ ዘእምቅድመ፡ ዓለም፡ ሀሎ፡ ኀይለ፡ ልዑለ፡ ይኬልልዎ፡ በስብሐት፡ …</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is crudely written in pencil.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title መዝምር is written on the back board with white paint.&#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script: e.g., fols. 93rb, 95rb.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign, in the shape of a cross (+) indicating the place where the omissions, written in the upper or left margin, belong: e.g., fols. 6vb, 22va, 29va (here in red pencil), 42ra, 57rb, 69rb, 73rb, 92vb, 103ra.&#xD;
- Omitted words inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 36va, 73rb.&#xD;
- Erasures: e.g., fols. 14va, 20va, 35vb, 57rb, 71ra.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections indicated by thin lines or dashes above and below the words: e.g., fols. 9ra, 23ra, 48va, 62vb, 92vb, 104rb.&#xD;
- Lacunae (spaces for rubrication left unfilled): e.g., fols. 15va, 36rb, 45ra, 51rb, 64ra, 85rb.&#xD;
- Musical notations inserted in pencil a secondary hand: fol. 67ra.&#xD;
- Directives for ministers crudely written in pencil in the upper margin: e.g., fols. 46v-47r, 72r-v.</item>
                     </list>
